{
  "texts": [
    "This involves anonymizing sensitive conversations, preventing misuse of data, and ensuring that interactions are handled with care to avoid re-traumatization.",
    "Systems handling sexualized violence should adhere to ALTAI's human-centric design principle, prioritizing user safety by avoiding the use of triggering language and providing helpful, accurate resources when users disclose experiences of violence.",
    "Developers should also include mechanisms that redirect users to professional support services when appropriate.Additionally, as legal frameworks around sexualized violence evolve, LLMs must be continuously updated to reflect current legal standards, including those outlined in the EU AI Act.",
    "The Act mandates regular testing and monitoring of AI systems to ensure compliance with evolving regulations.",
    "Similarly, ALTAI recommends ongoing assessments to ensure that AI systems remain accountable and aligned with ethical standards over time."
  ]
}